# rhdh-local/ Directory Protection

## This Directory is PRISTINE -- Do Not Modify

The `rhdh-local/` directory contains the official RHDH Local project cloned from `https://github.com/redhat-developer/rhdh-local.git`. It must remain unmodified to allow clean `git pull` updates.

## Rules

- **NEVER** edit files in this directory for customization purposes
- **NEVER** create new configuration files here (use `rhdh-customizations/` instead)
- **ALWAYS** verify: `cd rhdh-local && git status` should show "working tree clean" for tracked files
- Copied customization files (from `apply-customizations.sh`) are gitignored and do not affect tracked file status

## What to Do Instead

If you need to customize configuration:

1. Edit the corresponding file in `rhdh-customizations/`
2. Run `cd rhdh-customizations && ./apply-customizations.sh` to copy it here
3. Restart with `./down.sh && ./up.sh --customized [flags]`

## Exceptions

- **Upstream contributions**: Modify files here only when contributing changes back to the RHDH Local project
- **Temporary debugging**: Make temporary changes, but restore with `git checkout` when done
- **Reading/exploring**: Reading files here is always fine -- these are the defaults and examples

## Key Files (read-only reference)

- `compose.yaml` -- Base Docker Compose configuration
- `default.env` -- Default environment variables
- `configs/app-config/app-config.yaml` -- Default app configuration
- `configs/dynamic-plugins/dynamic-plugins.default.yaml` -- Default plugin configuration
- `wait-for-plugins-and-start.sh` -- RHDH entrypoint script
- `prepare-and-install-dynamic-plugins.sh` -- Plugin installer script
- `*.example.yaml` -- Templates for creating customizations
